    </blockquote>
    <p style="margin:clamp(44px,7vh,80px) auto 0;max-width:46ch;font-weight:380;font-size:clamp(19px,1.95vw,23px);line-height:1.7;color:#2B271F;">
      There&#8217;s a legend that in some cultures the camera was thought to steal a sliver of the soul. As a child I believed something close to it — that if I tore out the picture of the Earth, the one with the diagram of the crust, I would somehow be holding my own <em style="font-style:italic;">personal piece of Earth</em>.
    </p>
    <p style="margin:clamp(30px,4vh,44px) auto 0;max-width:46ch;font-style:italic;font-weight:300;font-size:clamp(15px,1.5vw,18px);line-height:1.66;color:#7E776A;">
      (And in case you&#8217;re wondering which five&#8209;year&#8209;old is busy dismantling diagrams of the planet — I was an ICSE kid, hopelessly fascinated by science and space.)
    </p>
